 C . 
  on April 14, 1865 . 
  The chair has been on display at The Henry Ford Museum in Dearborn, Michigan, for 85 years . 
  On April 15, it will be removed from its enclosure to be displayed in an open plaza for the 150th anniversary of the assassination . 
  The red chair has a stain on the back that historians say is oil from other people who sat in the chair before Lincoln  . 
  The president was shot by pro-Confederacy actor John Wilkes Booth in the theater . 
 